      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait what? i'm not looking for metaphors, i just want to fix the device. the wiring and reset didn't help though. could it be a software thing or like a power issue with the C-wire?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I apologize for the detour into goblin territory. In that case, let's focus on fixing the issue. A software problem or a power issue with the C-wire could be causing the temperature fluctuations. \n\nThe C-wire, also known as the common wire, is a crucial connection for the Nest thermostat to function properly. If the C-wire is loose or not providing a stable power supply, it could cause the thermostat to malfunction. You can try checking the C-wire connection and ensuring it's secure. If that doesn't work, you may need to contact Nest support to troubleshoot or replace the C-wire.\n\nIt's also possible that the issue is related to a software glitch or a firmware update. Nest thermostats can sometimes experience software issues that cause temperature fluctuations. You can try checking for any firmware updates and installing the latest version to see if that resolves the issue.\n\nIn any case, it's a good idea to contact Nest support to get their assistance in diagnosing and fixing the problem. They can help you determine the root cause and provide a solution to get your thermostat working smoothly again.",
