      "content": "A tight C-wire and up-to-date firmware should rule out any obvious hardware issues. In that case, let's dig deeper into the settings. One potential cause of random temperature fluctuations at night is the \"Auto-Schedule\" feature. If the Auto-Schedule is set to \"Auto\" mode, it can cause the thermostat to adjust the temperature based on a schedule that's not set, leading to sudden drops.\n\nYou can try disabling the Auto-Schedule feature and setting a custom schedule to see if that resolves the issue. Another possibility is that the \"Energy Saver\" feature is set to \"Auto\" mode, which can also cause the thermostat to adjust the temperature unexpectedly.\n\nAdditionally, you can check the \"Smart Recovery\" settings to see if they're enabled. Smart Recovery allows the thermostat to adjust the temperature slowly over a set period of time, which can sometimes cause fluctuations. If Smart Recovery is enabled, you can try disabling it to see if that resolves the issue.\n\nIt's also worth noting that some users have reported issues with the \"Temperature Offset\" setting, which can cause the thermostat to adjust the temperature by a set amount. If you're not using this feature, you can try disabling it to see if that resolves the issue",
